{"lemma":"فاسِ","slug":"فاسِ","root":"ف.#.س","root_slug":"ف-_-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-_-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32832","n32833"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"Fez (the capital city of the region of Fez-Meknes, Morocco)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fez, tarboosh","tags":["archaic"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Central Atlas Tamazight ⴼⴰⵙ (fas); linked to the region of the Central Atlas Mountains called ْفَازَاز (fāzāz), deriving either from a chronicled بَنُو فَازَازْ (banū fāzāz), ultimately associated with Central Atlas Tamazight ⴰⴼⵣⴰ (afza, “coarse, rough, hard, rocky”). The headwear is derived from Ottoman Turkish فس (fes) coined from the Moroccan city where it was popularized, itself from فَاس (fās)."},"ipa":["/faːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32832","headword_ar":"فَاَسَ","root":"fA^s","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^asN","text_ar":"فَاَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, S, O, Msb, K) him, or it, (S, O,) or a tree, (AHn, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^os","text_ar":"فَاْس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHn, S, M, O, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"him, or it, (M,) or a tree, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therewith:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he clave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"split,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, O,) a piece of wood, (M,) or one's head, (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therewith."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) a man (S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^os","text_ar":"فَاْس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate"},{"kind":"text","text":"wheat, or other food. (O, K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","O","K","AHn","Msb","TA","T"]},{"entry_id":"n32833","headword_ar":"فَاْسٌ","root":"fA^s","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain implement of iron,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one digs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of hoe;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus called in the present day;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally having a blade more long than wide, and a short handle; altogether resembling an adz:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Kr, M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one cuts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adz;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an axe;"},{"kind":"text","text":"both also thus called in the present day; more commonly the former;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used for cutting, cleaving, and splitting, trees and wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^asa","text_ar":"فَاَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for hewing, forming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fashioning, wood &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaduwmN","text_ar":"قَدُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) [applied also to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pickaxe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAquwrN","text_ar":"صَاقُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this word may be suppressed: (Msb:) it is of the fem. gender: (M, Msb, K:) the pl. (of pauc., O) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afow^usN","text_ar":"اَفْوُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, Msb, K) and (of mult., O)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuw^uwsN","text_ar":"فُوُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, Msb, K,) and, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuw^osN","text_ar":"فُوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^osu All~ijaAmi","text_ar":"فَاْسُ اللِّجَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain part of the bit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tongue of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"iron that stands up towards"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so I render here the particle"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hanak","text_ar":"حَنَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"against which it is made to press when the rein is drawn hard for the purpose of checking the horse]; (IDrd in his book on the Saddle and Bridle, [in one part of which he likens to it the tongue of a buckle,] S, M, A, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the iron that stands up in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akiymap","text_ar":"شَكِيمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is in the middle of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$kymp","text_ar":"شكيمة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoHalaAni","text_ar":"مِسْحَلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISh:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$kymp","text_ar":"شكيمة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the iron that lies across in the mouth, [i. e., the bit-mouth, or mouth-piece of the bit,] and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misoHal","text_ar":"مِسْحَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an iron [i. e. a ring of iron, one of a pair of rings which are inserted each into the other, in the place of our curbchain,] beneath the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hanak","text_ar":"حَنَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the part between the two sides of the lower jaw]: (IDrd:) or, as some say, [and among them Kr.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the transverse iron in the bit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) but this assertion requires consideration. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaluwku","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَلُوكُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnahu fiY AlkalaAmi kamaA yaEoliku Alfarasu faA^osa All~ijaAmi","text_ar":"لِسَانَهُ فِى الكَلَامِ كَمَا يَعْلِكُ الفَرَسُ فَاْسَ اللِّجَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one mumbles his tongue in speaking like as the horse moves about in his mouth the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fA^s","text_ar":"فاس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^osu Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"فَاْسُ الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^osu","text_ar":"فَاْسُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqafaA","text_ar":"القَفَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The edge of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamaHoduwap","text_ar":"قَمَحْدُوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinder part of the back of the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that projects above the back of the neck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the small protuberance above the back of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hinder part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qmHdwp","text_ar":"قمحدوة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^osu Alr~aHaY","text_ar":"فَاْسُ الرَّحَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protuberant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nether,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mill-stone, in the middle of which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the axis."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw, description of Ursa Minor.) ―         -b5-  And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaA^osu","text_ar":"الفَاْسُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Constellation of Ursa Minor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Idem, same place.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^osu Alfami","text_ar":"فَاْسُ الفَمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The extremity of the mouth, in which are the teeth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijoEalo h`*aA AlA^amora faA^osFA waAHidFA","text_ar":"اِجْعَلْ هٰذَا الاَمْرَ فَاْسًا وَاحِدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make thou this affair to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniform,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one way"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mode"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA^j","text_ar":"باج"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["M","Kr","A","K","Msb","O","S","ISh","IDrd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}